        <h1>P H O T O G R A P H Y</h1><br>
        <h2>📸 What is Photography?</h2>
        <p><strong>Photography is the art, science, and practice of capturing images using light. It can be done with cameras, smartphones, or other digital devices. A photograph freezes a moment in time, telling a story or conveying emotions.
        </strong></p>
        <h3>🧭 Why is Photography Important?</h3><br>
        <ul><li>Preserves memories (weddings, travel, family, etc.)</li>
        <li>Expresses creativity</li>
        <li>Documents reality (journalism, wildlife, events)</li>
        <li>Supports businesses (advertising, branding)</li>
        <li>Inspires emotions and awareness</li></ul><br>
        <h3>
             Types of Photography :
        </h3>
        <table>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Type</strong></td>
                <td><strong>Description</strong>
            </tr>
            <tr><td>Portrait</td>
            <td>Focuses on people — emotions, expressions</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Landscape</td>
            <td>Captures nature, scenery, outdoor spaces</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Wildlife</td>
            <td>Photographs animals in their natural habit</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Street</td>
            <td>Everyday life and people in public space</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Macro</td>
            <td>Close-up of small objects insects, flowers</td></tr>
        </table><br>
        <h2>🛠 Basic Photography Tips</h2><br>
        <h3>📷 1. Understand the Exposure Triangle</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <li>ISO – Controls light sensitivity</li>
                <li>Aperture (f/stop) – Controls depth of field</li>
                <li>Shutter Speed – Controls motion blur/freeze</li>
            </li>
        </ul><br>
        <h3>🧠 2. Composition Rules
        </h3>
        <ul>
            <li
            Rule of Thirds: Imagine a 3x3 grid, place subjects at intersections></li>
            <li>Leading Lines: Use natural lines to guide the eye</li>
            <li>framing: Use elements like windows or arches to frame the subject</li>
        </ul><br>
        <h3>🎨 3. Lighting Matters</h3>
        <ul>
            <liUse natural light when possible></li>
            <li>Golden Hour (shortly after sunrise or before sunset) offers beautiful light</li>
            <li>Avoid harsh midday light unless it's stylistic</li>
        </ul><br>
        <h2>🌐 Photography in the Digital Age</h2><br>
        <ul>
            <li>Shared instantly via social media (Instagram, Pinterest)</li>
            <li>Used in content creation (blogs, websites, ad</li>
            <li>Easy access via smartphones with powerful cameras</li>
